humbria. <strong>North West</strong> - Cumbria, Lancashire, Merseyside, Cheshire, Greater Manchester. <strong>South East</strong> - Sussex, Thames Valley, Hampshire, Surrey, Kent. <strong>South West</strong> - Dorset, Wiltshire, Gloucestershire, Avon and Somerset, Devon and Cornwall. <strong>Wales</strong> - Gwent, South Wales, Dyfed-Powys, North Wales. <strong>West Midlands</strong> - West Midlands, Staffordshire, Warwickshire, West Mercia. Yorkshire and Humberside - North Yorkshire, West Yorkshire, South Yorkshire, Humberside. (3) West Midlands constabulary are unable to supply any FTA warrant data from 1 April 2012. (4) Lincolnshire Police were unable to supply any data for Q4 of 2014 because of technical issues related to the introduction of a new warrant management system. Procedures for supplying the Ministry of Justice with data relating to FTA warrants have been revised to ensure that in future these data are captured. Data presented are for the first three quarters of 2014 only. Note: These data are reported to the Ministry of Justice by police forces. As such, they are not directly comparable with other data presented in the Criminal Statistics bulletin, which are returned directly from administrative data systems used by magistrates' courts and the Crown Court.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2016-10-26T15:38:07.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604148/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604148/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604148/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Arrest Warrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2016 to Question 47082, if she will provide a breakdown by region of the figures provided in that Answer.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","48951"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604149","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>Details of ministerial meetings with external companies are published on gov.uk.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2016-10-26T14:53:16.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604149/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604149/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604149/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many meetings Ministers of her Department have had with social media companies to discuss harmful online content since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","48860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604150","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>One year reoffending rates for the first cohort managed under our probation reforms will be published in the quarterly proven reoffending statistics bulletin in autumn 2017, available on <a href="http://gov.uk" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>. This will include those for Wales.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-26T16:30:21.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604150/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604150/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Reoffenders: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the re-conviction  rate is of offenders supervised by Working Links in Wales during the first 12 months following such supervision.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604151","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>All prisoners sentenced to 12 months or less in custody receive through the gate services from the Wales Community Rehabilitation Company (CRC), whilst they are in prison. This includes support with securing employment, finding accommodation, debt and finance advice and resettlement to their community. On their release prisoners will then be supervised by the Wales CRC or National Probation Service, dependent upon their risk of harm.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-26T11:33:13.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604151/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604151/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Prisoners' Release: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what resources are provided for the supervision of people released from jail following a sentence of 12 months or less in Wales.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604152","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>The administration of probation services across the Wales Community Rehabilitation Company (CRC) is changing. There will be three operational hubs located in Swansea, Cardiff and Colwyn Bay. Frontline delivery office locations will exist across Wales and the Wales CRC are establishing community hubs to provide and deliver collaborative partnership working.</p><p>All CRC providers set out an agreed operating model within their bid during the Transforming Rehabilitation competition. We are robustly managing the contracts to make sure the providers deliver services which reduce reoffending, protect the public and provide value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-26T11:03:00.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604152/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604152/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Probation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many offices Working Links has in Wales for the administration of probation services; and what the locations are of those offices.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604153","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>Contracts with the 21 Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) in England and Wales commenced in February 2015, and are of seven years duration. The Wales CRC is continuing to provide services in accordance with its contract, and is being robustly managed by our contract management team to make sure they fulfil their contractual obligations in relation to service delivery, reducing reoffending, protecting the public and providing value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-26T16:36:06.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604153/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604153/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Probation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will review the contract awarded to Working Links for the delivery of probation services in Wales.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604154","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-24","<p>Clause 173(3) of the Wales Bill provides that probation is reserved to the United Kingdom Parliament. The Government has no intention to devolve the provision of probation services to the National Assembly for Wales.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-24T08:44:41.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604154/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604154/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Probation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will devolve the provision of probation services to the National Assembly for Wales.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604155","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>All Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) are contractually required to maintain a professional and appropriately skilled workforce to deliver the services set out in their contracts. We robustly contract manage each CRC to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitment to maintain service delivery, reduce reoffending, protect the public and deliver value for money for taxpayers.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","48900","2016-10-26T11:21:03.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604155/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604155/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Probation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether Working Links are in dispute with staff unions of the probation services in Wales and on what issues.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604156","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>The Government is investing close to £1 billion to reform and digitise our courts and tribunals to deliver swifter and more certain justice.</p><p> </p><p>Technology will be at the forefront of our reforms but specific support will be provided to ensure tribunals remain accessible to all and physical hearings will continue to be used to resolve many cases.</p><p> </p><p>The impact assessment published alongside the Transforming our Justice System consultation paper sets out our estimate of potential savings from tribunal panel composition reform based on possible future scenarios.</p><p> </p><p>The panel composition reforms will ensure that the most appropriate panel is always selected to hear a case. As now, relevant expertise will always be available where needed, regardless of how a case is resolved. The Senior President of Tribunals will continue to determine when panel members are used.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2016-10-26T14:45:34.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604156/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604156/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Social Security Benefits: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the reasons are for the proposal to reduce the number of benefit appeal cases in which (a) an appellant can appear in person and (b) the panel includes a member with direct experience of the relevant benefit; and what cost savings are expected to arise from that change.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","48930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604157","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>All Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) are contractually required to maintain a professional and appropriately skilled workforce to deliver the services set out in their contracts. We robustly contract manage each CRC to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitment to maintain service delivery, reduce reoffending, protect the public and deliver value for money for taxpayers.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","48894","2016-10-26T11:21:03.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604157/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604157/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Probation: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether Working Links in Wales plan probation staff redundancies.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604158","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>In the 12 months to 31 March 2016, 89 per cent of offenders sentenced to a community order or suspended sentence order were allocated to a Community Rehabilitation Company and 11 per cent to the National Probation Service.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-26T16:08:13.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604158/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604158/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Court Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of new court orders were made by the courts and subsequently allocated to (a) community rehabilitation companies and (b) National Probation Service in England and Wales, for the most recent period for which figures are available.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604159","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>We are currently conducting a comprehensive review of the probation system. The review will consider the allocation of cases between the National Probation Service and Community Rehabilitation Companies but public protection is our top priority. We will not hesitate to take the necessary action to make sure our vital Transforming Rehabilitation reforms are being delivered to reduce reoffending, cut crime and prevent future victims.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-26T16:22:09.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604159/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604159/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Court Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will review the allocation of new court orders for supervision between the National Probation Service and community rehabilitation companies.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604160","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-10-26","<p>Working Links provides individual tailored rehabilitation programmes to the specific requirements of the offender.</p><p> </p><p>These are unique to the individual and therefore the cost of each rehabilitation programme varies.</p><p>We have given providers the flexibility to use both innovated and mandated programmes to do what works to reduce reoffending, and support offenders.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-10-26T10:53:36.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604160/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604160/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-10-17","Offenders: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the annual cost is of supervising an individual offender in Wales by Working Links for the most recent financial year for which figures are available.","true","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","48897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604161","Prime Minister","false","2016-10-25","<p>Details of Ministerial overseas travel is published quarterly and is available on the gov.uk website.</p><p> </p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2016-10-25T11:02:22.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604161/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604161/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-10-17","Prime Minister: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what overseas visits she has made since her appointment.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","48917"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604162","Prime Minister","false","2016-10-25","<p>A list of ministerial responsibilities has been published and can be found on the gov.uk website.</p><p> </p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2016-10-25T11:00:56.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604162/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604162/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-10-17","Departmental Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when she plans to make available a comprehensive list of ministerial responsibilities.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","48903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604163","Prime Minister","false","2016-10-20","<p>Details of Ministers’ meetings with external organisations, including with newspaper and other media proprietors, editors and senior executives, are published on a quarterly basis and made available on the gov.uk website.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2016-10-20T09:23:13.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604163/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604163/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-10-17","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, how many meetings she has had with social media companies to discuss harmful online content since May 2015.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","48864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604164","Prime Minister","false","2016-10-25","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the position on House of Lords Reform set out by the Deputy Leader of the House, my hon. Friend the Member for Northampton North (Michael Ellis) during the debate on 19 October 2016, Official Report, column 886.</p><p> </p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2016-10-25T11:03:59.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604164/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604164/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-10-17","House of Lords: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what her policy is on reform of the House of Lords.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","48956"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604165","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>Spending Review 2015 restated the funding envelope for delivery of HS2 at £55.7bn, in 2015 prices. This breaks down as £27.2bn for Phase 1 (including rolling stock), £3.7bn for Phase 2a, and £24.8bn for Phase 2b (including rolling stock). We do not provide funding breakdowns for specific items such as stations due to commercial sensitivities.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:30:57.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604165/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604165/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether any detailed breakdown is available for (a) the redevelopment of Birmingham Curzon Station and (b) other costs of High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604166","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-20","<p>The Department has provided a grant payment of £70,000 to Driver First Assist for its 2016-17 programme.</p><p> </p><p>Driver First Assist is a not for profit organisation training large goods vehicle drivers to provide lifesaving first aid and manage the scene at a road traffic collision prior to the arrival of the emergency services. So far the organisation has trained 738 drivers to act as first responders.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-10-20T14:03:54.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604166/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604166/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","Large Goods Vehicle Drivers: First Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will detail how his Department provides support for a not-for-profit training programme for drivers in administering first aid; and how many drivers this programme has trained.","false","Biography information for Dr Alasdair McDonnell","Belfast South","Dr Alasdair McDonnell","48980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604167","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-20","<p>The case for aviation expansion is clear – but it’s vitally important we get the decision right so that it will benefit generations to come. As well as progressing the package of further work announced previously, the government is considering the Commission’s evidence before reaching a view on its preferred scheme this month.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-10-20T14:54:43.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604167/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604167/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","Airports: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to make an announcement on runway expansion in the South East.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","49041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604168","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-20","<p>In my capacity as Roads Minister, I will be visiting different parts of the strategic road network around the country over ‎the coming months.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-10-20T14:09:10.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604168/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604168/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","A595","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will visit the A595 in Copeland.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","48986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604169","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>All Non-Executive members including the Non-Executive Chair of the HS2 Ltd Board are appointed by the Secretary of State for Transport. All Executive Members of the HS2 Ltd Board are appointed by HS2 Ltd on the delegated authority from the Secretary of State. The Chief Executive Officer of the HS2 Ltd Board is appointed by the Chair of HS2 Ltd.</p><p> </p><p>All Ministerial appointments, extensions and exemptions to the HS2 Ltd Board, come under the remit of the Office for Commissioner for Public Appointments (OCPA). They are made using the process from the Commissioner’s Code of Practice for Ministerial Appointments to Public Bodies. The Commissioner may, in exceptional circumstances, agree that Departments may depart from this Code where he believes that this is justified in the public interest.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:24:31.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604169/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604169/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed Two","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what method and criteria were used to select the Board of HS2 Ltd.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604170","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-24","<p>The Department does not restrict what claimants can spend their mobility allowance on. Whilst the Department has a role in determining who is eligible for the Motability scheme, it is claimants’ own choice whether or not to join. Therefore the Department does not have a target for the number of people using the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is responsible for the civilian disability benefits that passport to Motability, Personal Independence Payment (PIP) and Disability Living Allowance (DLA). However, there are more people with a Motability vehicle now than there were when PIP was first introduced; the last major change to such benefits.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-24T14:48:02.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604170/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604170/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604170/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Motability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether his Department plans to take steps to reverse the decline in the number of Motability users.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","48863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604171","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The Government is committed to improving the rights of disabled people when accessing and using transport. Though Government cannot currently comment on the Law Commission’s proposals as it continues to scrutinise the report, we are implementing measures to improve the transport rights of disabled people. These include sections 165 and 167 of the Equality Act 2010, and a strengthening of Taxi and Private Hire Vehicle Best Practice Guidance for local authorities, both of which are expected in 2017.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T12:44:35.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604171/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604171/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604171/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","Department for Transport: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has made an assessment of the implications for its policies of the Extra Costs Commission, initiated by the disability charity Scope in July 2014.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","48861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604172","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>There is currently no evidence linking driverless vehicles and future demand for rail.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-10-25T08:18:17.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604172/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604172/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","Driverless Vehicles: Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether any assessment has been made of the effect of driverless vehicles on future demand for extra rail capacity.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604173","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>High Speed 2 will be a fully electrified railway.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:01:10.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604173/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604173/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604173/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether High Speed 2 will be a fully electrified railway line.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604174","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The business case for HS2 assumes the same fares structure as today. It is too early to set individual fares for HS2 services, which will begin operation in 2026.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:05:31.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604174/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604174/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604174/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will estimate the cost of a single ticket to any destination served by High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604175","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The Government is considering how best HS2 services should be provided both when operating on the new High Speed and conventional rail networks. This includes consideration of franchising options but does not rule out alternative routes for service delivery, to ensure that services deliver the Government objectives for HS2, and optimum use is made of total capacity across the entire network to maximise the benefits for passengers and secure a return for taxpayers on the significant investment Government is making in HS2<em>. </em>No final decision has been taken.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:10:51.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604175/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604175/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will allow the completed High Speed 2 railway line to be open access as opposed to restricted by franchise.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604176","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>Birmingham and the West Midlands will be key beneficiaries of HS2, which will provide a springboard for regeneration and growth and support job creation.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport alongside the Department for Communities and Local Government are supporting Birmingham and have provided £2.5 million funding to support the development of the Greater Birmingham &amp; Solihull Growth Strategy. The strategy demonstrates the potential for HS2 to support the creation of 36,000 jobs around Curzon Street Station and 16,500 jobs around Birmingham Interchange Station.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, HS2 Ltd expects the construction of HS2 to create 24,600 jobs, which will include many further opportunities for Birmingham and the West Midlands.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:17:42.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604176/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604176/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether an estimate has been made of the number of jobs likely to be created due to the completion of the station for High Speed 2 in Birmingham.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604177","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>Under the terms of the Freedom of Information Act (2000) if a contractor or another party holds information on behalf of the public authority then it is considered to be held by the public authority and therefore subject to the FOIA.</p><p> </p><p>HS2 Ltd have a clause in all of their contracts which states that information that contractors hold as part of the HS2 contract is subject to the FOIA.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T12:48:58.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604177/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604177/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether any of the contractors undertaking construction or management of the building works on High Speed 2 will be subject to public Freedom of Information requests.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","48820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604178","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>Greater Manchester Combined Authority and Manchester Airports Group have made a commitment in principle to a local contribution to funding for the airport station and we continue to work with them on the details.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T12:52:04.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604178/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604178/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Manchester Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made on securing a suitable funding package for the Manchester Airport interchange on the High Speed 2 line.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604179","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The funding envelope of £55.7 billion for delivering HS2 does not rely on EU grant funding. HS2 was awarded a grant of €39 million from the Connecting Europe Facility (CEF) for ground investigation works. My Department will work with HM Treasury to see if this should be covered by the government’s commitment to provide continuity of funding for participants in EU programmes (announced by my Right Honourable Friend, the Chancellor of the Exchequer on the 13th August). I refer my Right Honourable Friend to my response of the 15th September, UIN 46680, (<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=46680" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=46680</a>).</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T12:55:29.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604179/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604179/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Government plans to substitute any funding for High Speed 2 that was part of an EU grant.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604180","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The Department for Transport has not produced estimates of the expected impact on property prices in the areas surrounding HS2 terminals.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:21:30.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604180/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604180/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate has been made of changes in property prices in and around (a) all major High Speed 2 terminals and (b) Birmingham High Speed 2 terminal.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604181","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>No private funding contributions have been secured for HS2 to date.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T12:58:10.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604181/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604181/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much private funding has been secured for the High Speed 2 project from major corporate beneficiaries to date.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604182","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The assessment of the M4 relief road around Newport is being considered by the Welsh Government.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-10-25T08:09:28.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604182/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604182/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604182/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","M4","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has used the Tempro 7 system to make revised calculations of traffic flows on the proposed M4 relief road.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","48812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604183","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-20","<p>The Department for Transport conducts a roadside survey every two years. This survey estimates the number of vehicles without a valid licence or Statutory Off Road Notification (SORN) to determine the rate of vehicle excise duty evasion.</p><p> </p><p>The last survey took place in June 2015, which was eight months after the DVLA stopped issuing paper tax discs. The survey estimated that 1.4% of vehicles on UK roads were unlicensed and were not subject to a SORN.</p><p> </p><p>The DVLA aims to make vehicle excise duty easy to pay and hard to avoid and operates a comprehensive package of measures to tackle vehicle excise duty evasion. These measures range from reminder letters, penalties and court prosecutions through to the use of Automatic Number Plate Recognition cameras, wheel clamping and the removal of unlicensed vehicles.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-20T15:02:20.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604183/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604183/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","Motor Vehicles: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many car owners whose car tax has expired have not made a SORN declaration since the tax licence disc was abolished in 2015.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","48874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604184","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The Department and High Speed 2 Limited continue to develop technical and economic analysis on HS2. The Government intends to announce a decision on the route of Phase 2b by the end of the year. This will be supported by a Strategic Outline Business Case.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T13:27:27.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604184/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604184/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made on the technical and economic analysis required for a full route decision on Phase 2b of High Speed 2; and when the deadline is for details of that route to be announced.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604185","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>Yes, the £70 million allocated to the Road Safety, Community and Environment, and Business and Local Economy Funds is included within the overall £55.7 billion funding envelope for HS2.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-10-25T15:35:50.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604185/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604185/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the £55.7 billion agreed funding for the High Speed 2 project includes the costs of the recently proposed £70 million road safety and support fund for communities affected by the line.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604186","Department for Transport","false","2016-10-25","<p>The Government is considering the impacts of the decision to leave the European Union, including future arrangements for existing legislation. Until the UK leaves, EU law continues to apply, so we continue to comply with the existing directives and regulations, such as the common rules on compensation and assistance under Regulation (EC) 261/2004.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-10-25T08:13:11.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604186/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604186/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-10-17","Aviation: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the Government's policy is on whether the provisions of EU Directive 261/2004, on compensation for denied boarding, cancellation or long delays for air passengers, should continue to apply in the UK (a) until and (b) after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","48912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604187","Women and Equalities","false","2016-11-02","<p>The Government has already carried out a consultation on the future of civil partnerships in 2014, and has no plans to carry out another consultation on this issue.</p><p>Following the passage of the Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013, we carried out a full review of the operation and future of the Civil Partnership Act 2004, which included a thorough public consultation on potential changes to civil partnership. Views were invited on three options: abolishing civil partnerships; phasing them out; or extending them to opposite sex couples.</p><p>The review found that there was no clear consensus on the future of civil partnerships. A majority of respondents to the consultation were against extending civil partnerships to opposite sex couples and a significant number of stakeholders thought it was too soon to consider making changes to civil partnerships until the impact of extending marriage to same sex couples is known. Given the lack of any consensus, the Government has no current plans to make changes to the Civil Partnership Act 2004.</p><p>The Isle of Man is a self-governing crown dependency. We are not required to carry out an assessment on their legislation.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","48964","2016-11-02T17:58:19.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604187/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604187/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-10-17","Civil Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, if she will bring forward proposals for a consultation on extending civil partnerships to heterosexual couples in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","48963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604188","Women and Equalities","false","2016-11-02","<p>The Government has already carried out a consultation on the future of civil partnerships in 2014, and has no plans to carry out another consultation on this issue.</p><p>Following the passage of the Marriage (Same Sex Couples) Act 2013, we carried out a full review of the operation and future of the Civil Partnership Act 2004, which included a thorough public consultation on potential changes to civil partnership. Views were invited on three options: abolishing civil partnerships; phasing them out; or extending them to opposite sex couples.</p><p>The review found that there was no clear consensus on the future of civil partnerships. A majority of respondents to the consultation were against extending civil partnerships to opposite sex couples and a significant number of stakeholders thought it was too soon to consider making changes to civil partnerships until the impact of extending marriage to same sex couples is known. Given the lack of any consensus, the Government has no current plans to make changes to the Civil Partnership Act 2004.</p><p>The Isle of Man is a self-governing crown dependency. We are not required to carry out an assessment on their legislation.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","48963","2016-11-02T17:58:19.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604188/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604188/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-10-17","Civil Partnerships: Isle of Man","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what assessment she has made of the consequences for her policies of the introduction of different-sex civil partnerships on the Isle of Man.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","48964"
