"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604190","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-20","<p>DWP has received no representations on migrant employees in the UK being forced to repay funds paid to them as a result of shortfalls in wages to their employers upon return to their country of origin.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-10-20T15:57:07.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604190/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604190/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Migrant Workers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what representations he has received on migrant employees in the UK being forced to repay funds paid to them as a result of shortfalls in wages to their employers upon return to their country of origin; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","48989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604191","Department for Work and Pensions","true","2016-10-20","<p><del class="ministerial">DWP has received no representations on migrant employees in the UK being forced to repay funds paid to them as a result of shortfalls in wages to their employers upon return to their country of origin.</del></p><p><ins class="ministerial">DWP has not made an estimate of the number of foreign companies employing migrant workers in the UK who have sued their employees for overpayment of wages upon their return to their country of origin.</ins></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-10-20T15:39:20.617Z","2016-10-21T11:31:20.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604191/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604191/answer","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604191/answer/previousversion/15529","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Migrant Workers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether he made an estimate of the number of foreign companies employing migrant workers in the UK who have sued their employees for overpayment of wages upon their return to their country of origin.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","48990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604192","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-20","<p>There is no condition based entitlement to Employment Support Allowance.</p><p>We will be working over the coming months with medical professionals and other stakeholders to develop functional criteria that will help us identify those with the most severe health conditions or disabilities, for whom repeat work capability assessments can be stopped.</p><p>Rather than a list of specific medical conditions, the criteria will be based on identifying claimants with the most severe health conditions or disabilities where it would be unreasonable to expect the individual to undertake any form or amount of work or work-related activity. This change will only apply to those placed in the Support Group and UC equivalent.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","48979","2016-10-20T10:39:35.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604192/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604192/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Work Capability Assessment: Chronic Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the announcement of 1 October 2016 that people with long-term degenerative conditions will be exempt from repeat work capability assessments, if he will set out those medical conditions a diagnosis for which will provide such exemption.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","48978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604193","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-20","<p>The Pensions Regulator is independent, and how it uses its powers is a matter for the regulator. The Secretary of State and I regularly meet the independent Pensions Regulator about a variety of matters.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2016-10-20T14:48:00.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604193/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604193/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","British Steel: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions he has had with the Pensions Regulator on using its powers to oblige Tata Steel to increase its support for the British Steel Pension Scheme.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","48991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604194","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-20","<p>There is no condition based entitlement to Employment Support Allowance.</p><p>We will be working over the coming months with medical professionals and other stakeholders to develop functional criteria that will help us identify those with the most severe health conditions or disabilities, for whom repeat work capability assessments can be stopped.</p><p>Rather than a list of specific medical conditions, the criteria will be based on identifying claimants with the most severe health conditions or disabilities where it would be unreasonable to expect the individual to undertake any form or amount of work or work-related activity. This change will only apply to those placed in the Support Group and UC equivalent.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","48978","2016-10-20T10:39:35.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604194/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604194/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Work Capability Assessment: Chronic Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the announcement of 1 October 2016 that people with long-term degenerative conditions will be exempt from repeat work capability assessments, if he will confirm that that exemption will apply to people who have been found eligible for employment and support allowance and who have a diagnosis of (a) motor neurone disease or (b) Parkinson's disease.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","48979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604195","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-20","<p>The number of people in employment is increasing and the latest figures show that the employment rate has remained at the record high of 74.5%. There are more people in work than ever before (31.81 million) – up 106,000 on the quarter and 560,000 on the year.</p><p>The number of long term unemployment is 443,000 – the lowest level since 2008.</p><p>Universal Credit, the Work Programme and the Jobcentre Plus Offer, is reforming the welfare system to improve incentives and provide more effective support to those without work.</p><p>Work Coaches have the flexibility to offer all claimants a comprehensive menu of help which includes skills provision and job search support. All claimants who are long term unemployed can access the tailored, back to work support on offer from the Work Programme, which provides support for those who are more at risk of long-term unemployment.</p><p>An Employment and Health Related Service is being launched in 2017. The Work and Health Programme is a new programme that will harness the expertise of private, public, voluntary and community sector providers to deliver sustained work for disabled people, disadvantaged groups and the long term unemployed.</p><p>There is also to be a new Youth Obligation from April 2017. From day 1 of their claim, young people will participate in an intensive support regime equipping them with vital skills to not only find a job, but build capability to sustain work. After six months they will be expected to apply for an appropriate apprenticeship, a traineeship, gain work skills or go on a mandatory work placement to give them the opportunities they need to get on in work.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-10-20T16:29:51.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604195/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604195/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Long Term Unemployed People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to help reduce long-term unemployment.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","48996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604196","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-20","<p>The consultation “Self-sufficient local government: 100% business rates retention”, published by the Department for Communities and Local Government, sought views on a range of options for devolving new responsibilities to local government in England including more responsibility for caring for older people. This was not a consultation on the devolution of Attendance Allowance.</p><p>If changes were to be considered in respect of Attendance Allowance for England and Wales, there would be further consultation and any proposals would be discussed with the Welsh Government.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-20T13:30:23.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604196/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604196/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Attendance Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 12 October 2016 to Question 47504, whether the Welsh Government has agreed to take responsibility for attendance allowance.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","48976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604197","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-24","<p>The Government recognises that people need support that is tailored to their needs. Personal Budgets are currently being trialled in Access to Work to offer customers greater flexibility to manage their Travel to Work or Support Worker costs. Initial findings from the trial are expected in early 2017.</p><p>A Personal Budgets model was previously tested in the Right to Control Trailblazers, which ran from 2010 to 2013. Disabled people taking part in the trailblazers were offered greater choice and control over the support they received, as well as the option to take a direct payment and arrange their own support. The final evaluation report did not find any evidence that the Right to Control Trailblazers had a significant positive impact on customers, both overall and by subgroup.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-24T14:12:58.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604197/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604197/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Employment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if his Department will carry out a trial of the introduction of personal budgets for employment support for disabled people.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","49008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604198","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-24","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-10-24T15:32:54.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604198/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604198/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many GP reports were provided as supporting evidence to a universal credit application by universal credit applicants in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","48904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604199","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-20","<p>My Department is currently considering further changes to employer debt legislation, following a Call for Evidence about section 75 employer debt in non-associated multi-employer schemes last year with a view to consulting on any specific proposals in due course.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2016-10-20T14:41:53.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604199/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604199/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Pension Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he plans to publish the response to the Government's consultation on section 75 employer debt in pension funds, published in March 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","48888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604200","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-25","<p>Any suggestion to add diseases to the prescribed list is first considered by the Industrial Injuries Advisory Council. The Secretary of State then considers this advice, taking into account potential impacts and any other relevant considerations.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-25T10:46:32.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604200/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604200/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Industrial Injuries Disablement Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will bring forward proposals for secondary legislation to revise the list of medical conditions covered by the industrial injuries disablement benefit.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","48931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604201","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-24","<p>The regulation of work-based pension schemes, including the funding regime is a matter for the independent Pensions Regulator. The Secretary of State and I regularly meet with the Regulator about a variety of matters, including section 75.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2016-10-24T13:50:49.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604201/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604201/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Pension Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what discussions the Government has held with the Pensions Regulator on section 75 employer debt in pension funds.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","48872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604202","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-24","<p>We welcome the Sense report, Realising Aspirations for All. We want all disabled people and those with a long term health condition to fulfil their potential and achieve their aspirations.</p><p>Everyone has an important part to play in making the transformative changes required for long-term reform on supporting disabled people into work and contributing to halving the disability employment gap.</p><p>We will soon publish a Green Paper that will explore a range of options for long-term reform across different sectors enabling everyone to realise their aspirations, regardless of their health condition or disability. We are engaging with a range of stakeholders, including organisations that represent the needs of deafblind people, through our preparatory work and detailed consultation plans that will follow.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-24T14:48:10.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604202/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604202/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Employment: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the findings in the Report from the charity Sense, Realising Aspirations for All; and what steps he is taking to ensure that people who are deafblind and those with complex needs benefit from plans to halve the disability employment gap.","false","Biography information for Maria Caulfield","Lewes","Maria Caulfield","48808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604203","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-10-24","<p>We welcome the publication of the final report from the Extra Costs Commission. Businesses have their part to play by developing innovative products and services for disabled people. My officials will work with Scope (who are taking on the work of the Commission) as they tackle their next priorities of the insurance and energy markets.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-10-24T15:16:45.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604203/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604203/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-10-17","Department for Work and Pensions: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether his Department has made an assessment of the implications for its policies of the Extra Costs Commission, initiated by the disability charity Scope in July 2014.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","48862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604204","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-25","<p>I can confirm that the department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, has responsibility for Land Registry. As Parliamentary Under Secretary of State, Minister for Small Business, Consumers and Corporate Responsibility, Land Registry forms part of my portfolio.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-10-25T08:19:24.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604204/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604204/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-17","Land Registry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department has responsibilities for the Land Registry; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","48857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604205","HM Treasury","false","2016-10-20","<p>Paragraph 21(1) of Schedule 3, Part 5 of the Equality Act 2010 makes clear that it is not a contravention of the Act for insurers to make decisions on the grounds of disability provided they do so by reference to information from a reliable source that is relevant to the risk to be insured, and that it is a reasonable decision. The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) expects firms to comply with relevant legislation, including the Equality Act, and can undertake its own enquiries to better understand what the firm is doing and whether any of its regulatory requirements have been breached.</p><p> </p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-10-20T11:37:33.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604205/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604205/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-17","Insurance: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will request that regulators investigate whether disabled people have access to insurance that fairly reflects risk.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","48865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604206","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-20","<p>The Department is in close contact with Nissan as part of its responsibility to actively manage the relationship with our major manufacturers.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-10-20T16:04:48.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604206/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604206/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-17","Nissan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with Nissan on its future investment in the UK after the UK's exit of the EU.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","48849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604207","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-10-24","<p>As the Government stated at the outset of the competition, the intention of Phase One was to gauge market interest among global market actors in developing, commercialising and financing Small Modular Reactor Competitions in the UK. The evidence gathered during Phase One is being used to inform policy decisions, including the design of any future stages of the competition. Given that Phase One is still continuing, I am not able to provide any further information at this stage.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2016-10-24T09:21:36.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604207/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/604207/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-10-17","Nuclear Reactors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he plans to hold a second phase of the Small Modular Reactor Competition; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","48929"
